        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Introducing Col. Charles Caldwell, of Kentucky.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            


<p><placeName>Nachitoches </placeName><date when="1822-03-14">14th March 182</date>2</p>
<p>Dear Sir</p>

<p>I take the liberty of introducing to your friendly attentions 
<persName>Col. charles Caldwell of <placeName>Kentucky</placeName></persName>, he visits your Country with the
view of establishing himself therein.<pb n="484"/></p>

<p><persName>Col. Caldwell</persName>'s having no acquaintance in <placeName>St Antonio</placeName> has induced
me take this freedom, which indeed I consider unnecessary, his
gentlemanly address could not fail of procuring him the Esteem of
all those with whom he may become acquainted.</p>

<p>I shall consider any attentions you may please to extend to <persName>Col.
Caldwell</persName> as conferred on myself&#8212;Wishing you much happiness,
and great success in your great enterprise</p>

<p><persName>James C Carr</persName></p>

<p><persName>Judge Austin</persName></p>


        </div1>
